= RSpec Changelog

== Version 0.5.4 (in SVN)
Release notes go here

* Removed references to --sugar, which is now gone (underscores are enabled by default) [aslak_hellesoy]
* Removed --doc and added --formatter and --dry-run [aslak_hellesoy]
* Refactored towards more pluggable formatters [aslak_hellesoy]
* Refactored simple_text_reporter's io logic to separate class, to ease html generation [aslak_hellesoy]
* Use webgen's execute tag when generating website (more accurate) [aslak_hellesoy]
* Fixed incorrect quoting of spec_opts in SpecTask [aslak_hellesoy]
* Added new option --sweet/-s to enable underscored shoulds like 1.should_equal(1) - patch from Rich Kilmer [aslak_hellesoy]
* Removed most inherited instance method from Mock, making more methods mockable. [aslak_hellesoy]
* Made the RCovVerify task part of the standard toolset. [aslak_hellesoy]
* Documented Rake task and how to use it with Rcov [aslak_hellesoy]
* Implemented <ruby></ruby> tags for website (hooking into ERB, RedCloth and syntax) [aslak_hellesoy]
* RSpec Rake task now takes spec_opts and out params so it can be used for doc generation [aslak_hellesoy]
* RCov integration for RSpec Rake task (#4058) [aslak_hellesoy]
* Group all results instead of prinitng them several times (#4057) [aslak_hellesoy]
* Remove mock.rb from backtrace [aslak_hellesoy]
* Mocks can now yield [aslak_hellesoy]
* should.not.raise reports actual error rather than specified error class [dchelimsky]
* backtrace shows context name and spec name [dchelimsky]
* backtrace can run in quiet or verbose mode [dchelimsky]
* errors in setup or teardown are reported as happening in setup or teardown (not in the specification) [dchelimsky]
* split examples into examples (passing) and failing_examples [dchelimsky]

== Version 0.5.3
The "hurry up, CoR is in two days" release.

* Don't run rcov by default [aslak_hellesoy]
* Make separate task for running tests with RCov [aslak_hellesoy]
* Added Rake task to fail build if coverage drops below a certain threshold [aslak_hellesoy]
* Even more failure output cleanup (simplification) [dchelimsky]
* Added duck_type constraint for mocks [dchelimsky]

== Version 0.5.2
This release has minor improvements to the commandline and fixes some gem warnings

* Readded README to avoid RDoc warnings [aslak_hellesoy]
* Added --version switch to commandline [aslak_hellesoy]
* More changes to the mock API [dastels], [dchelimsky]

== Version 0.5.1
This release is the first release of RSpec with a new website. It will look better soon.

* Added initial documentation for API [dastels]
* Added website based on webgen [aslak_hellesoy]
* Modified test task to use rcov [aslak_hellesoy]
* Deleted unused code (thanks, rcov!) [aslak_hellesoy]
* Various changes to the mock API [dastels], [dchelimsky]
* Various improvements to failure reporting [dchelimsky]

== Version 0.5.0
This release introduces a new API and obsolesces previous versions.

* Moved source code to separate subfolders
* Added new DSL runner based on instance_exec
* Added spike for testdox/rdoc generation
* merge Astels' and Chelimsky's work on ShouldHelper
* this would be 0.5.0 if I updated the documentation
* it breaks all of your existing specifications.  We're not sorry.

== Version 0.3.2

The "srbaker is an idiot" release.

* also forgot to update the path to the actual Subversion repository
* this should be it

== Version 0.3.1

This is just 0.3.0, but with the TUTORIAL added to the documentation list.

* forgot to include TUTORIAL in the documentation

== Version 0.3.0

It's been a while since last release, lots of new stuff is available.  For instance:

* improvements to the runners
* addition of should_raise expectation (thanks to Brian Takita)
* some documentation improvements
* RSpec usable as a DSL

== Version 0.2.0

This release provides a tutorial for new users wishing to get started with
RSpec, and many improvements.

* improved reporting in the spec runner output
* update the examples to the new mock api
* added TUTORIAL, a getting started document for new users of RSpec

== Version 0.1.7

This release improves installation and documentation, mock integration and error reporting.

* Comparison errors now print the class name too.
* Mocks now take an optional +options+ parameter to specify behaviour.
* Removed __expects in favour of should_receive
* Added line number reporting in mock error messages for unreceived message expectations [aslak_hellesoy].
* Added should_match and should_not_match [aslak_hellesoy].
* Added a +mock+ method to Spec::Context which will create mocks that autoverify (no need to call __verify) [aslak_hellesoy].
* Mocks now require names in the constructor to ensure sensible error messages [aslak_hellesoy].
* Made 'spec' executable and updated usage instructions in README accordingly [aslak_hellesoy].
* Made more parts of the Spec::Context API private to avoid accidental usage [aslak_hellesoy].
* Added more RDoc to Spec::Context.

== Version 0.1.6

More should methods.

* Added should_match and should_not_match [aslak_hellesoy].

== Version 0.1.5

Included examples and tests in gem [aslak_hellesoy].

== Version 0.1.4

More tests on block based Mock expectations.

== Version 0.1.3

Improved mocking:

* block based Mock expectations.

== Version 0.1.2

This release adds some improvements to the mock API and minor syntax improvements

* Added Mock.should_expect for a more consistent DSL [aslak_hellesoy].
* Added MockExpectation.and_returns for a better DSL [aslak_hellesoy].
* Made Mock behave as a null object after a call to Mock.ignore_missing [aslak_hellesoy]
* Internal syntax improvements [aslak_hellesoy].
* Improved exception trace by adding exception class name to error message [aslak_hellesoy].
* Renamed some tests for better consistency [aslak_hellesoy].

== Version 0.1.1

This release adds some shoulds and improves error reporting

* Added should_be_same_as and should_not_be_same_as [aslak_hellesoy].
* Improved error reporting for comparison expectations [aslak_hellesoy].

== Version 0.1.0

This is the first preview release of RSpec, a Behaviour-Driven Development library for Ruby 

* Added Rake script with tasks for gems, rdoc etc [aslak_hellesoy].
* Added an XForge task to make release go easier [aslak_hellesoy].
